column19: First mobile Quadro based on the GeForce2 Go, Dynamic core clock 100–143 MHz, dynamic voltage 1.575V, graphics core listed as 64-bit and 128-bit for DDR and SDR SDRAM types respectively according to Nvidia

column20: Based on the GeForce4 Go, dynamic core clock 66–220 MHz, core voltage 1.35 V, uses DDR SDRAM according to Nvidia brochures

column19: Based on GeForce4 Go 4200, uses DDR according to Nvidia brochures
Based on the Geforce FX Go (FX 56XX)
Seems to be an overclocked Quadro FX 700 Go.

column14: Last chip designated as a Quadro FX Go, uses PCIe instead of AGP 8×.  Core config has been mentioned as either 8:5:8:8 or 12:5:12:12 - the latter is likely since chip is derived from GeForce Go 6800.
